Can you modify the C++ code provided below to generate the first 20 Fibonacci numbers, using the formula that involves the golden ratio? You need to provide a step-by-step explanation, including the calculations necessary to obtain the correct output. To make it more challenging, you are only allowed to use logical reasoning and cannot use any arithmetic operations or variables (e.g. n, sqrt5, phi, psi) directly. Additionally, you need to use a table of values to assist you in generating the Fibonacci numbers. The table contains the values for the first 10 Fibonacci numbers, which can be used as a reference to generate the remaining 10 numbers. Can you solve this puzzle? 
C++ Code:
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int main()
{
   int n, first = 0, second = 1, next, i;
   cout << "Enter the number of terms you want: ";
   cin >> n;
   cout << "First " << n << " terms of Fibonacci series are: ";
   for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
   {
      if (i <= 1)
         next = i;
      else
      {
         next = first + second;
         first = second;
         second = next;
      }
      cout << next << " ";
   }
   return 0;
}

