How can I simulate and compare the performance of a web server and an application server in handling multiple client requests and ensuring security?
To simulate and compare performance, I can use MATLAB to create a script that sends HTTP requests to both a web server and an application server and measures the response time for each request. I can also incorporate security measures such as SSL encryption and authentication protocols in the script to compare how each server handles security features.
Here is an example MATLAB code for sending HTTP requests to a web server:
url = 'http://www.example.com';
options = weboptions('Timeout', 5);
response = webread(url, options);
And here is an example MATLAB code for sending HTTP requests to an application server:
url = 'http://www.example.com/app';
options = weboptions('Timeout', 5, 'CertificateFilename', 'cert.pem', 'KeyFilename', 'key.pem');
