How can I calculate the cost of apples for different quantities and under different scenarios using PHP code? Please provide the PHP code for the following scenarios:
1. The cost of 1 kg of apples is $2. Calculate the cost of 5 kg, 10 kg, and 15 kg of apples.
2. Assume the cost of 1 kg of apples is $2. What would be the cost of 3 kg of apples if the cost of apples increases by 25%? Please provide the answer in a table format.
[PHP code]
<?php
//Scenario 1: Cost of apples for different quantities
$cost_per_kg = 2; //cost of 1 kg of apples
$quantity = array(5, 10, 15); //quantities in kg
echo "<table>";
echo "<tr><th>Quantity (kg)</th><th>Cost</th></tr>";
foreach($quantity as $q){
  $cost = $q * $cost_per_kg;
  echo "<tr><td>$q</td><td>$cost</td></tr>";
}
echo "</table>";
//Scenario 2: Cost of apples if the cost increases by 25%
$cost_per_kg = 2; //cost of 1 kg of apples
$increase_percent = 25; //increase in percentage
$quantity = 3; //quantity in kg
$cost = $quantity * $cost_per_kg;
$increase_amount = ($cost * $increase_percent) / 100;
$new_cost = $cost + $increase_amount;
echo "<br><br><table>";
echo "<tr><th>Quantity (kg)</th><th>Old Cost</th><th>25% Increase</th><th>New Cost</th></tr>";
echo "<tr><td>$quantity</td><td>$cost</td><td>$increase_amount</td><td>$new_cost</td></tr>";
echo "</table>";
?>

