What is the MATLAB code to calculate the average monthly increase in market capitalization of Apple Inc. based on the given data below? And assuming the average monthly increase in market capitalization remains constant, what will be the market capitalization of Apple Inc. in November 2020 and February 2021?
Here is the MATLAB code to calculate the average monthly increase in market capitalization of Apple Inc.:
```matlab
% Market Capitalization data
Dates = {'August 2020', 'May 2020', 'March 2020', 'January 2020', 'November 2019'};
MarketCap = [2.18, 1.40, 1.11, 1.39, 1.17];
% Convert dates to serial date numbers
DateNum = datenum(Dates, 'mmm yyyy');
% Calculate monthly increase in market capitalization
MonthlyIncrease = diff(MarketCap) ./ diff(DateNum);
% Calculate average monthly increase from Jan 2020 to Aug 2020
AvgMonthlyIncrease = mean(MonthlyIncrease(DateNum(2:end)>=datenum('Jan 2020') & DateNum(2:end)<=datenum('Aug 2020')));
% Predict market capitalization in Nov 2020 and Feb 2021
DateNumNov2020 = datenum('Nov 2020', 'mmm yyyy');
MarketCapNov2020 = MarketCap(end) + AvgMonthlyIncrease * (DateNumNov2020 - DateNum(end));
MarketCapNov2020 = round(MarketCapNov2020 / 100) * 100;
DateNumFeb2021 = datenum('Feb 2021', 'mmm yyyy');
MarketCapFeb2021 = MarketCap(end) + AvgMonthlyIncrease * (DateNumFeb2021 - DateNum(end));
MarketCapFeb2021 = round(MarketCapFeb2021 / 100) * 100;
% Display results
fprintf('The average monthly increase in market capitalization from Jan 2020 to Aug 2020 is $%.2f billion.\n', AvgMonthlyIncrease);
fprintf('The predicted market capitalization of Apple Inc. in Nov 2020 is $%.2f billion.\n', MarketCapNov2020);
fprintf('The predicted market capitalization of Apple Inc. in Feb 2021 is $%.2f billion.\n', MarketCapFeb2021);
```

